[[cdo:11 nguŏk 9 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:11 goe̍h 9 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:十一月初九]] {{Lunisolar November}} '''November 9''' is the 9th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * In the 14th year of the Tianbao era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} [[755]] – {{ill|December 16|ja|12月16日|12=draft}}): The An Shi Rebellion erupted. In the Tang Dynasty, the military governor ({{ill|Jiedushi|ja|節度使|12=draft}}) An Lushan and his subordinate Shi Siming rose in revolt, plunging the empire into civil strife. * In the 12th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1635]] – {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日|12=draft}}): The Tokugawa shogunate established the Temple and Shrine Commissioner ({{ill|Jisha Bugyō|ja|寺社奉行|12=draft}}). * In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1637]] – {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日|12=draft}}): The Tokugawa shogunate dispatched Itakura Shigemasa and others to suppress the Shimabara Rebellion. * In the 5th year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1872]] – {{ill|December 9|ja|12月9日|12=draft}}): The Meiji government decided to abolish the traditional lunisolar (Taiyin-Taiyang) calendar—effective from the day after December 2 of that year—and adopt the solar calendar.
