'''November 9''' is the 9th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝}}.

== Events ==
* In the 14th year of the Tianbao era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[755]] – {{ill|December 16|ja|12月16日}}): The An Shi Rebellion erupted. In the Tang Dynasty, the military governor ({{ill|Jiedushi|ja|節度使}}) An Lushan and his subordinate Shi Siming rose in revolt, plunging the empire into civil strife.
* In the 12th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1635]] – {{ill|December 18|ja|12月18日}}): The Tokugawa shogunate established the Temple and Shrine Commissioner ({{ill|Jisha Bugyō|ja|寺社奉行}}).
* In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1637]] – {{ill|December 25|ja|12月25日}}): The Tokugawa shogunate dispatched Itakura Shigemasa and others to suppress the Shimabara Rebellion.
* In the 5th year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1872]] – {{ill|December 9|ja|12月9日}}): The Meiji government decided to abolish the traditional lunisolar (Taiyin-Taiyang) calendar—effective from the day after December 2 of that year—and adopt the solar calendar.

