== Events == * In the 14th year of the Tianbao era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[755]] – [[:en:December 16|December 16]]): The An Shi Rebellion erupted. In the Tang Dynasty, the military governor ([[:en:Jiedushi|Jiedushi]]) An Lushan and his subordinate Shi Siming rose in revolt, plunging the empire into civil strife. * In the 12th year of the Kan'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1635]] – [[:en:December 18|December 18]]): The Tokugawa shogunate established the Temple and Shrine Commissioner ([[:en:Jisha-bugyō|Jisha Bugyō]]). * In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1637]] – [[:en:December 25|December 25]]): The Tokugawa shogunate dispatched Itakura Shigemasa and others to suppress the Shimabara Rebellion. * In the 5th year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] – [[:en:December 9|December 9]]): The Meiji government decided to abolish the traditional lunisolar (Taiyin-Taiyang) calendar—effective from the day after December 2 of that year—and adopt the solar calendar.
