== Events ==
* In the 14th year of the Tianbao era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|755|en|755|WD=Q23650|lt=755|1=755}} – {{ill|December 16|en|December 16|WD=Q2410|lt=December 16|1=December 16}}): The An Shi Rebellion erupted. In the Tang Dynasty, the military governor ({{ill|Jiedushi|en|Jiedushi|WD=Q1688932|lt=Jiedushi|1=Jiedushi}}) An Lushan and his subordinate Shi Siming rose in revolt, plunging the empire into civil strife.
* In the 12th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1635|en|1635|WD=Q6879|lt=1635|1=1635}} – {{ill|December 18|en|December 18|WD=Q2438|lt=December 18|1=December 18}}): The Tokugawa shogunate established the Temple and Shrine Commissioner ({{ill|Jisha-bugyō|en|Jisha-bugyō|WD=Q1036279|lt=Jisha Bugyō|1=Jisha-bugyō}}).
* In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1637|en|1637|WD=Q6889|lt=1637|1=1637}} – {{ill|December 25|en|December 25|WD=Q2745|lt=December 25|1=December 25}}): The Tokugawa shogunate dispatched Itakura Shigemasa and others to suppress the Shimabara Rebellion.
* In the 5th year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} – {{ill|December 9|en|December 9|WD=Q2304|lt=December 9|1=December 9}}): The Meiji government decided to abolish the traditional lunisolar (Taiyin-Taiyang) calendar—effective from the day after December 2 of that year—and adopt the solar calendar.

